HEADWORD: Equisonance
<hw>E*quis"o*nance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Equi-</ets> + L. <ets>sonans</ets>, p. pr. of sonare to
sound: cf. F. ⟦eacute⟧quisonnance. See <er>Sonant</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An equal sounding; the consonance of the unison
and its octaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equisonant</ent>⟦br⟧
